---

!! Node shapes

|!Syntax|!Shape|
|`root((text))`|Circle — conventional for root|
|`node[text]`|Square / rectangle|
|`node(text)`|Rounded rectangle|
|`node)text(`|Cloud shape|

!! Tips

* Indentation defines the hierarchy. Each level of indent becomes a child of the line above it.
* There is exactly one root node per diagram.
* Mindmaps do not support clickable links or events.
* Keep labels short — overlapping text is a known layout limitation.

